metadata.name: dim_policy_status
metadata.comment:
The 'dim_policy_status' table contains information about the status of various travel policies. It includes details such as the creation date, policy type, and whether the policy is active or canceled. This data can be used to track policy statuses, monitor policy cancellations, and analyze policy trends. It can also help in identifying potential issues with specific policy types or regions. This information can be useful for those in travel management, policy administration, and compliance roles.

metadata.name: mng_params
metadata.comment:
The 'mng_params' table contains various parameters used in the management of travel programs. It includes details such as the parameter name, its value, and whether it has been checked by QDA or business. This data can be used to manage and monitor the parameters of travel programs, ensuring compliance with regulations and optimizing their performance. It can also be used to track changes in parameter values and their impact on travel programs.
